Exeter High School Students/Parents:

Emails were sent out to all students in the spring for students to choose options for their classes this fall.

1) Please check your email and make sure you have completed your survey so we can get your schedule put into SIS360

2) Next week you should be able to login to your SIS 360 app on your phone or computer to view your current schedule.

3) Thursday August 13th from 10:00 AM to 6:00 PM students may enter the building to meet with one of the counselors in order to finalize their schedules or pick up their schedules
and chromebooks

4) We are excited to begin the new school year with in-person instruction

shared_text:
Exeter Tiger Athletics
July 24 at 10:15 AM ·

Mandatory parent/athlete meeting on Friday, August 7.
Grades 7-8 will be at 5:00 PM
Grades 9-12 will be at 6:00 PM

This will be our beginning of the year athletic meeting but will have important information about guidelines for the 2020-2021 in regards to athletics.

If your child will be entering 7th grade and they plan to participate in athletics they will need to have a physical.

If your child participated in athletics and activities last year grades 7-12 your child will need updated emergency information, medical history information, and insurance information. You will be able to update this information on August 7.

Fall HS practice (9-12) will begin August 10.
Fall MS practice (7-8) will begin August 17.

If you have any questions please feel free to reach out to Ms. Fly (afly@exeter.k12.mo.us).

post_text:
School starts on Tuesday, August 25th, and we are working diligently to develop a plan to begin school safely. Information at the state level is constantly being updated, and we are continuing to revise our plans to fit our students and community. Nonetheless, we want you to know that we are taking the safety of our students, teachers, and community members very seriously. We are very excited to have students and teachers back in the school building learning and growing everyday.

We will be reaching out to gather more information from parents and teachers in the form of a survey. Then, we will finalize our re-entry plan and communicate it out to everyone.

Every Day is a great day to be a Tiger

Due to the Governor’s extension of phase one until June 15th, the Exeter School District has decided to postpone Senior graduation until Friday, June 19th at 7:00PM.

8th Grade graduation will be Monday June 22nd at 7:00 PM

Preschool graduation will be Tuesday, June 23rd at 6PM
KINDERGARTEN graduation will be Tuesday, June 23rd at 7:00 PM

At this point we will still be practicing social distancing and a limited number of guests per graduate. We will communicate these details with the families when we receive more guidance from the state and local levels.

Thank you to everyone who made this presentation possible for our graduates. During the development of this presentation students were met with individually in order to be in compliance with social distancing guidelines. This presentation was developed to honor our graduates virtually on the original date and time scheduled for Commencement. Exeter School District plans to have an official graduation ceremony on Friday, June 5 at 7:00 PM.

Special thanks to:
Photo and video producer- Zoe Brown
Videographer- Dustin Foster
Senior Sponsor- Aubrey Hill
Photographer/Organizer- Jeanetta McCammon

post_text: Thank you to our food service professionals for always doing a great job! We appreciate you!
shared_text:
Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education
May 1 at 7:00 AM ·

Today, we celebrate "School Lunch Hero Day!" Between preparing healthy food, adhering to strict nutrition standards, navigating student food allergies, and offering service with a smile, Missouri nutrition professionals have a lot on their plate on a “normal” day. Extended building closures during COVID-19 required our food service professionals to quickly be innovative and creative to develop ways to continue feeding the Missouri students who rely on school breakfast and lunch each day.

Join us in recognizing these important team members today!

post_text:
A note from Mr. Pisanti-

If you're in one of my biology classes,

Tomorrow morning (Wednesday the 15th) at 10 AM, I will be hosting an online video meeting, either through Zoom or Google Meet, for anybody who would like some help with this week's assignment. I'll have a few new examples that we can go through, and we'll go through the slides and see if there's a spot that gives a lot of trouble.

I apologize for the lateness of this reminder - I posted about a meeting in a comment on Google Classroom last night. Usually Classroom sends e-mails when I comment like that, but did not this time.

If you don't see this in time, that's perfectly okay. It's not going to hurt you at all if you don't attend the meeting. If you don't attend and hit some trouble, make sure you e-mail me and tell me specifically what's messing you up (I check my mail lots of times throughout the day).

I hope everybody's doing okay and staying safe through the remainder of the wellness break. I look forward to seeing you online tomorrow.

Mr. Pisanti

A word from Mrs. Brattin:

My assignments for MS Language Arts for this week (4/13 due 4/20) are posted in Google Classroom and available in paper packet form in the lunch pick up line at Exeter School.

The paper packet from previous weeks are also there in case they are needed. Paper packets can be returned to school. I will come pick them up there.

April is National Poetry Month, so each class is reading a poem and constructing a poem. There is also a reading/writing survey included.

Please remind students to check their email for reminders and check-ins every so often.

I miss all my students and I wish them and their families well-being and happy times! Just remember, some days are better than others. And, we are all in this together! ❤️ #ItsalwaysagreatdaytobeaTIGER! #wearitwithpride! #roar 🐯

Best wishes for a great week! ❤️🐯✏️🤓🐯✏️🤓

My assignments for MS Language Arts for this week are now posted in Google Classroom and available in paper packet form in the lunch pick up line at Exeter School.

The paper packet from last week is also there in case you were unable to pick it up. If students can work on Google classroom, great! If they need a paper packet because they do not have internet, it is there. These paper packets can be returned in the lunch pick up line as well. Ms. Fly returns them to my mailbox.

If you are unable to get to school, and do not have internet access at home, please send me a message and I will put it in the USPS mail to you.

The assignments are the same, in either paper or Google classroom.

I am tagging parents and grandparents that I am friends with. Please spread the word. I am always available through email or Facebook messenger if there are any questions.

My work is a review of reading and writing concepts we have covered in class this year. I hope they find it interesting and thought provoking. I miss them all!

Best wishes for a great week! ❤️🐯✏️🤓🐯✏️🤓

Exeter Fire Protection District
March 12 at 8:05 PM ·

Last week we had the privilege of working with Exeter School District to put together a fire safety class for the entire school! Traditionally every year we talk with students during fire prevention week in October and we will continue to do so! However we felt it necessary to take on the task of refreshing and educating the whole school. Simple fire safety and planning is often forgotten about and not implemented like it should! We appreciate Exeter School for helping us with the planning and coordinating to get the whole school involved! If you have any questions about fire safety, planning, or need smoke alarms just send us a message!
